# TypeScript Style

## No type assertions (`as` is banned by lint)
Validate/narrow instead of asserting.

```ts
// BAD
const data = json as Product;

// GOOD - runtime-validated, single source of truth
const data = Product.parse(json);

// GOOD - object literal checked against a type
const config = { port: 3000 } satisfies ServerConfig;
```

## Function declarations for named functions/components
```ts
// BAD
const getTotal = (lines: CartLine[]) => ...;

// GOOD
function getTotal(lines: CartLine[]): number { ... }
```
Inline callbacks (`arr.map((x) => x.id)`) are fine.

## Modern APIs
Use `??`, `?.`, template literals; never `var`; prefer `const`.

## Exhaustive discriminated unions
```ts
switch (error.code) {
  case "SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE": return ...;
  case "INSUFFICIENT_STOCK": return ...;
  default: {
    const _exhaustive: never = error.code;
    throw new Error(`Unhandled: ${_exhaustive}`);
  }
}
```
